onal_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an extremely long time\", \"from\": 4322, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 4382, \"to\": 4387}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 4397, \"to\": 4404}, {\"ngram\": \"the country\", \"from\": 4408, \"to\": 4419}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4466, \"to\": 4468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Laghouag credited France's success in part due to their reliance on French-bred horses, saying that out of eight or nine horses in Toyko, seven of them were French-bred.\", \"from\": 4472, \"to\": 4641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4490, \"end\": 4496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9670016259001047, \"rank\": 0.02970911661235282, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Laghouag\", \"from\": 4472, \"to\": 4480}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 4510, \"to\": 4514}, {\"ngram\": \"their reliance\", \"from\": 4522, \"to\": 4536}, {\"ngram\": \"French-bred horses\", \"from\": 4540, \"to\": 4558}, {\"ngram\": \"eight or nine horses\", \"from\": 4579, \"to\": 4599}, {\"ngram\": \"Toyko\", \"from\": 4603, \"to\": 4608}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have a team with an incredible level, and so for this kind of event like this Olympics we have really good results even though we are never winners before the end, and obviously we are looking forward to [the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics] in order to win gold over Great Britain,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4643, \"to\": 4933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4909, \"end\": 4922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999867067355341, \"rank\": 1.0883724247444075e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 4652, \"to\": 4658}, {\"ngram\": \"an incredible level\", \"from\": 4664, \"to\": 4683}, {\"ngram\": \"this kind\", \"from\": 4696, \"to\": 4705}, {\"ngram\": \"event\", \"from\": 4709, \"to\": 4714}, {\"ngram\": \"this Olympics\", \"from\": 4720, \"to\": 4733}, {\"ngram\": \"really good results\", \"from\": 4742, \"to\": 4761}, {\"ngram\": \"winners\", \"from\": 4787, \"to\": 4794}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 4802, \"to\": 4809}, {\"ngram\": \"[the 2028 Los Angeles Olympics\", \"from\": 4851, \"to\": 4881}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 4886, \"to\": 4891}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 4899, \"to\": 4903}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The team who was perhaps most emotional was the one from Japan, comprised of Kazuma Tomoto (Vinci De La Vigne), Yoshiaski Oiwa (MGH Grafton Street), Ryuzo Kitajima (Cekatinka) and Toshiyuki Tanaka (Jefferson).\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 5144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4992, \"end\": 4997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9997961335318927, \"rank\": 0.00019766893881583916, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 5057, \"end\": 5061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yotsuya_Kaidan\", \"score\": 0.9505628427119881, \"rank\": 0.052008299785066193, \"text\": \"Oiwa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yotsuya_Kaidan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yotsuya_Kaidan\"}, {\"begin\": 5063, \"end\": 5066, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monumenta_Germaniae_Historica\", \"score\": 0.648578160320048, \"rank\": 0.5418342170295997, \"text\": \"MGH\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monumenta_Germaniae_Historica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Monumenta_Germaniae_Historica\"}, {\"begin\": 5067, \"end\": 5081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grafton_Street\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grafton Street\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grafton_Street\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grafton_Street\"}, {\"begin\": 5133, \"end\": 5142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0768973013149053e-21, \"text\": \"Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The team\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 4943}, {\"ngram\": \"Kazuma Tomoto\", \"from\": 5012, \"to\": 5025}, {\"ngram\": \"(Vinci De La Vigne\", \"from\": 5026, \"to\": 5044}, {\"ngram\": \"Cekatinka\", \"from\": 5100, \"to\": 5109}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They finished cross-country in bronze-medal position, but at this morning's horse inspection, Kitajima's mount Cekatinka was sent to the hold box and was subsequently withdrawn.\", \"from\": 5145, \"to\": 5322, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"country\", \"from\": 5165, \"to\": 5172}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze-medal position\", \"from\": 5176, \"to\": 5197}, {\"ngram\": \"this morning's horse inspection\", \"from\": 5206, \"to\": 5237}, {\"ngram\": \"Kitajima's mount Cekatinka\", \"from\": 5239, \"to\": 5265}, {\"ngram\": \"the hold box\", \"from\": 5278, \"to\": 5290}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That meant they earned 20 penalties for substituting in Tanaka and Jefferson for show jumping.\", \"from\": 5323, \"to\": 5417, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5379, \"end\": 5385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Masahiro_Tanaka\", \"score\": 0.9999985830973889, \"rank\": 1.416829005477284e-06, \"text\": \"Tanaka\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Masahiro_Tanaka\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Masahiro_Tanaka\"}, {\"begin\": 5390, \"end\": 5399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.0768973013149053e-21, \"text\": \"Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"20 penalties\", \"from\": 5346, \"to\": 5358}, {\"ngram\": \"show jumping\", \"from\": 5404, \"to\": 5416}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But thanks to all three riders jumping clear over fences, they added just 2 time penalties to their score to finish on a 115.8 to take the bronze medal.\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5570, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all three riders\", \"from\": 5432, \"to\": 5448}, {\"ngram\": \"fences\", \"from\": 5468, \"to\": 5474}, {\"ngram\": \"just 2 time penalties\", \"from\": 5487, \"to\": 5508}, {\"ngram\": \"their score\", \"from\": 5512, \"to\": 5523}, {\"ngram\": \"the bronze medal\", \"from\": 5553, \"to\": 5569}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The finish was historic for Japan, marking the team's first equestrian team medal and first eventing medal in Olympic history, and only its second equestrian Olympic medal ever-the first coming almost a century ago, whenTakeichi Nishi rode Uranus to individual show jumping goldin the 1932 Los Angeles Olympics.\", \"from\": 5572, \"to\": 5883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5600, \"end\": 5605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9997961335318927, \"rank\": 0.00019766893881583916, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}, {\"begin\": 5632, \"end\": 5642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9999999998544808, \"rank\": 1.45502853